title: A1466 820-3437-B no power
message:
Hi, I have an A1466 820-3437-B that the client report that stoped working without no reason

I have green light, fan spin, CPU gets hot, and get voltages on big coils.

I have:

PP5V_S0 = 5V
PP3V3_S0 = 3.3V
PP3V3_SUS = 3.3V
PP1V05_SUS =1.06V
PP1V5_S0 = 1.5V
PPVCC_S0_CPU = 1.74V

Can it be BIOS?
Can you help?[B][/B]

title: A1466 820-3437-B no power
message:
Could be BIOS, even bad CPU.
Check first if PLT_RESET_L is high.
Also check for USB activity.

title: A1466 820-3437-B no power
message: PLT_RESET_L  is high (3.3V) and no USB activity

title: A1466 820-3437-B no power
message:
II should have done something wrong in the first flash. 

After re-flashed bios I get fan spin, but no USB  activity.  
PLT_RESET_L  = 3.3V, CPU gets hot and it consume arround 0.550 V on PSU

title: A1466 820-3437-B no power
message:
Check all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and their traces.
Also check the resistors from LPC bus.
